---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import HeroVideo from '../components/HeroVideo.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us"
  description="Learn about the Otter Valley Rod & Gun Club — 50 acres of shooting sports near Straffordville, Ontario."
>

  <HeroVideo
    compact
    backgroundImage="/images/club/clubhouse-01.jpg"
    title="About Us"
    tagline="50 Acres of Tradition Since Day One"
  />

  <!-- Club History -->
  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="text-center">Our History</h2>
      <hr class="gold-divider" />
      <div class="prose-block">
        <p>
          Located along Plank Road (formerly Hwy #19) between Eden and Straffordville in Elgin County,
          the Otter Valley Rod &amp; Gun Club sits on 50 acres of forested countryside. The club
          serves the shooting sports, archery, and fishing community of southwestern Ontario.
        </p>
        <p>
          Today the property includes four trap fields, a 13-station sporting clays course, a
          200-yard rifle range with 15 covered stations, indoor and outdoor handgun ranges, indoor
          and outdoor archery facilities, and a stocked fishing pond. The clubhouse serves as the hub
          for league nights, events, and member gatherings.
        </p>
        <p>
          In 2007&ndash;2008, the club received an Ontario Trillium Foundation grant that funded
          significant accessibility upgrades and facility enhancements, including pond renovation.
          The club is built and maintained by its volunteer membership.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Facility Overview -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="text-center">Our Facilities</h2>
      <hr class="gold-divider" />
      <div class="grid-3 facilities-grid">

        <div class="card facility-card">
          <div class="facility-img-wrap">
            <img src="/images/ranges/trap-01.jpg" alt="Trap fields" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <h3>Trap Shooting</h3>
          <p>
            Four trap fields accommodate everything from casual practice rounds to registered
            competitions. Shoot singles, doubles, and handicap across well-maintained fields
            with manual and automatic target options.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card facility-card">
          <div class="facility-img-wrap">
            <img src="/images/ranges/sporting-clays-01.jpg" alt="Sporting clays course" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <h3>Sporting Clays</h3>
          <p>
            Thirteen stations wind through the natural terrain of the property, presenting
            a wide variety of target presentations. The course is designed to challenge
            shooters of every skill level and changes regularly to keep the experience fresh.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card facility-card">
          <div class="facility-img-wrap">
            <img src="/images/ranges/rifle-01.jpg" alt="200-yard rifle range" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <h3>Rifle Range</h3>
          <p>
            A 200-yard outdoor rifle range with covered shooting benches provides an ideal
            setting for zeroing optics, load development, and long-range target practice.
            Range flags and safety protocols are strictly observed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card facility-card">
          <div class="facility-img-wrap">
            <img src="/images/ranges/handgun-01.jpg" alt="Handgun ranges" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <h3>Handgun Ranges</h3>
          <p>
            Both indoor and outdoor handgun ranges serve IPSC competitors, police and
            security professionals, and recreational pistol shooters. Baffled berm
            design ensures a safe shooting environment year-round.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card facility-card">
          <div class="facility-img-wrap">
            <img src="/images/ranges/archery-01.jpg" alt="Archery ranges" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <h3>Archery</h3>
          <p>
            Indoor lanes and an outdoor 3D archery course with life-size foam targets
            scattered through the woods offer bowhunters and target archers an authentic,
            varied practice experience in every season.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card facility-card">
          <div class="facility-img-wrap">
            <img src="/images/pond/fishing-pond-01.jpg" alt="Stocked fishing pond" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <h3>Fishing Pond</h3>
          <p>
            A privately stocked fishing pond on the property gives members and their
            families a peaceful place to cast a line. The pond is maintained throughout
            the season and is a favourite spot for families with young anglers.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Property -->
  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid-2 property-grid">
        <div class="property-text">
          <h2>The Property</h2>
          <hr class="gold-divider" style="margin-left: 0;" />
          <p>
            The club sits on 50 acres of wooded Ontario countryside along Plank Road
            (formerly Highway 19), midway between the communities of Eden and
            Straffordville in Elgin County. The forested setting is more than just a
            backdrop — it shapes the character of the club. Tree lines define range
            corridors, natural terrain informs the sporting clays course layout, and
            the quiet of the woods is itself a reason many members keep coming back.
          </p>
          <p>
            The property includes a well-equipped clubhouse available for member use,
            league nights, and club events. Ample parking, clean washrooms, and
            shaded gathering areas make it a comfortable destination for a full day
            of shooting or a quick afternoon session.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="property-image-wrap">
          <img
            src="/images/club/grounds-aerial-01.jpg"
            alt="Aerial view of Otter Valley Rod and Gun Club property"
            loading="lazy"
            class="property-img"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Accessibility -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="accessibility-block">
        <div class="accessibility-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9854;</div>
        <div>
          <h2>Accessibility</h2>
          <hr class="gold-divider" style="margin-left: 0;" />
          <p>
            The clubhouse and many of the shooting facilities at Otter Valley are
            handicap accessible. Significant accessibility upgrades were completed in
            2007–2008 with generous support from the Ontario Trillium Foundation,
            ensuring that members and visitors of all abilities can participate fully
            in the club's activities. We are committed to maintaining and improving
            accessible access across the property.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you have specific accessibility requirements or questions before your
            first visit, please reach out to us at
            <a href="mailto:ovrag@hotmail.com">ovrag@hotmail.com</a> — we're happy
            to help make arrangements.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Photo Grid -->
  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="text-center">A Closer Look</h2>
      <hr class="gold-divider" />
      <div class="photo-grid">
        <img src="/images/club/clubhouse-01.jpg" alt="Otter Valley clubhouse" loading="lazy" class="photo-grid-img" />
        <img src="/images/club/grounds-aerial-01.jpg" alt="Aerial view of the grounds" loading="lazy" class="photo-grid-img photo-grid-wide" />
        <img src="/images/club/grounds-02.jpg" alt="Club grounds" loading="lazy" class="photo-grid-img" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Join CTA -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2>Ready to Join?</h2>
      <hr class="gold-divider" />
      <p style="max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;">
        Become a member of Otter Valley Rod &amp; Gun Club and gain full access to all
        ranges, facilities, and the community that makes this club what it is.
      </p>
      <a href="/membership/" class="btn btn-gold">View Membership Options</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Prose block */
  .prose-block {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .prose-block p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  /* Facilities grid */
  .facilities-grid {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .facility-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .facility-img-wrap {
    width: 100%;
    height: 200px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--brown-dark);
  }

  .facility-img-wrap img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    transition: transform 0.5s ease;
  }

  .facility-card:hover .facility-img-wrap img {
    transform: scale(1.04);
  }

  .facility-card h3,
  .facility-card p {
    padding: 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .facility-card h3 {
    margin-top: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  .facility-card p {
    padding-bottom: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.93rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Property section */
  .property-grid {
    align-items: center;
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  .property-text p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .property-image-wrap {
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--brown-light);
  }

  .property-img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 380px;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }

  /* Accessibility */
  .accessibility-block {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .accessibility-icon {
    font-size: 3rem;
    color: var(--gold);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .accessibility-block p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* Photo grid */
  .photo-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .photo-grid-img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 240px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border: 1px solid var(--brown-light);
    display: block;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .photo-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr;
      align-items: stretch;
    }

    .photo-grid-img {
      height: 280px;
    }

    .photo-grid-wide {
      height: 280px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .accessibility-block {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .accessibility-icon {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
